    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-31T18:00:00-05:00" n="294"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d294">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Four Power Pact/18: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atherton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-31T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 31, 1933—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>61. For Davis. Your 62, March 31, 3 p.m. The Italian Ambassador<note n="23"
                        xml:id="d294fn23">Augusto Rosso.</note> has left with me a brief résumé of
                    the proposed agreement.<note n="24" xml:id="d294fn24">Not printed.</note>
                    <pb facs="0503" n="401" xml:id="pg_401"/>
                    <hi rend="italic">New York Times</hi>, under London date line today, carries
                    purported full text from “trustworthy source”. Article 4 contains references to
                    Colonial cooperation not mentioned in Italian Embassy’s outline. Unless you can
                    ascertain that the <hi rend="italic">Times</hi> story is substantially accurate,
                    please cable full text as given by Grandi.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
